==English==
{{wikipedia|Polabian language}}

===Etymology===
From the name of Polabian tribes, which in turn derives from the name of the Elbe river in Slavic languages: {{term|Łaba|lang=pl}} in Polish and {{term|Labe|lang=cs}} in Czech.

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# West [[Slavic]] [[language]], extinct in 18th century.

